cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.ROB, cs.CE 

This paper presents a concept of a mobile robotic system consisting of multiple wheeled mobile agents constrained by a passive kinematic chain. The paper focuses on the optimization framework for forward simulation and kinematic control of this system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the modularity and adaptability of the system, which could fall under cs.ROB (Robotics) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
